# Event Planning Board — AI Agent Rules
# Applies to: Cursor, Claude, GitHub Copilot

## MANDATORY RULES (never violate)

### 1. No external dependencies
- FORBIDDEN: databases (SQLite, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Redis)
- FORBIDDEN: external HTTP APIs, cloud services, ORMs
- ALL storage must use In-Memory collections (dict, list)
- EXCEPTION: pytest, pytest-cov for testing only

### 2. Interfaces before implementation
- Every service class MUST implement a defined interface (ABC)
- Every repository MUST extend IRepository[T]
- NEVER inject concrete classes — always inject interfaces

### 3. Test-Driven Development (TDD)
- Write tests BEFORE or SIMULTANEOUSLY with implementation
- Every new method requires at least one test
- Edge cases (empty input, None, negative values) MUST be tested
- Coverage threshold: 70% minimum (target: >90%)

### 4. SOLID principles — mandatory
- S: Each class has ONE responsibility
- O: Extend via Strategy/Observer, don't modify existing classes
- L: Subtypes must be substitutable for base types
- I: Prefer small, focused interfaces
- D: Depend on abstractions (IRepository, IStrategy), not concretions

### 5. GoF Design Patterns — mandatory
- Strategy: ALL algorithms (priority scoring, budget warnings) via ITaskPriorityStrategy / IBudgetWarningStrategy
- Observer: ALL notifications via EventBus + IEventObserver
- Adding new patterns requires updating docs/diagrams/

### 6. Code style
- Type hints on ALL function signatures
- Docstrings on all public methods and classes
- No magic numbers — use named constants or Enum values
- Max function length: 30 lines; max class: 200 lines

## PROJECT STRUCTURE — strictly follow

src/models/        — dataclasses only, NO business logic beyond simple state
src/services/      — business logic, depends on repository interfaces
src/storage/       — IRepository implementations (InMemory only)
src/utils/         — Strategy, Observer, helpers

tests/unit/        — one test file per module, mock dependencies
tests/integration/ — end-to-end scenarios using shared_context fixture

## FORBIDDEN PATTERNS (anti-patterns)

- God classes: classes doing everything
- Hard-coded strings for event types, status — always use Enum
- Direct instantiation of repositories inside services — inject them
- Test code without assertions
- Catching generic Exception without re-raising or logging

## WHEN GENERATING TESTS

- Use pytest fixtures from tests/conftest.py
- For integration tests: use shared_context fixture (ensures shared EventBus)
- Mock only external I/O — never mock your own domain logic
- Name tests: test_<method>_<scenario>_<expected_result>
- Always test: happy path, None input, empty collections, boundary values
